Sirada Thamwanna, 29, said she was exhausted after winning the four kilometre foot race with her soon-to-be groom Sittichai Prasongsin, 27."Just now, I told the groom that I was going to give up, I can't do it anymore," Sirada said after crossing the finish line in a white wedding dress and black running shoes."He supported me and said that we only had a little more to go," she added.The free wedding package includes a gown for the bride and suit for the groom, wedding bands, a honeymoon on the Thai resort island of Phuket and a trip to the Maldives.